The third Riyadh International Humanitarian Forum (RIHF3) will take place on Monday, bringing together government officials, practitioners and key decision makers of the humanitarian sector. The theme of the forum this year is “Evolving Humanitarian Needs: development and response.” The event will focus on addressing the most pertinent issues of the current global humanitarian challenges. There will be discussions on the importance of developing, strengthening and delivering humanitarian assistance according to the highest standards of quality and efficiency to affected populations worldwide. The event will hold case study presentations by researchers from regions affected by humanitarian crises.